cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.SD 

This paper discusses the integration of two semantic annotation schemes, UCCA and preposition supersenses, for natural language processing tasks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with natural language processing. The paper also involves machine learning and parsing, which are relevant to sub-categories such as cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the empirical evaluation of the integrated representation, which is relevant to sub-categories such as cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing).
